{"id":5117,"date":"2026-02-28T08:27:38","date_gmt":"2026-02-28T02:57:38","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/?page_id=5117"},"modified":"2026-02-28T09:21:34","modified_gmt":"2026-02-28T03:51:34","slug":"sb_11-10-19-association-quick-way-to-learn-from-experiences-chanting-easy-to-realize-krsna","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/sb\/11\/10\/19\/","title":{"rendered":"SB_11.10.19 &#8211; Association &#8211; quick way to learn from experiences &#038; Chanting &#8211; easy to realize\u00a0Krsna !\u00a0"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<iframe title=\"SB_11.10.19 - Association - quick way to learn from experiences &amp; Chanting - easy to realize Krsna !\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" src=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/embed\/dMqWjuuWIB0?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" referrerpolicy=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\" allowfullscreen><\/iframe>\n<\/div><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Srimad&nbsp;Bhagavatam \u2013 11.10.19 | HH Bhanu Swami Maharaj | ISKCON Chennai | April 7, 2021&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><em>&#8220;Om Namo&nbsp;Bhagavate&nbsp;Vasudevaya&#8221;<\/em>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><em>&#8220;Om Namo&nbsp;Bhagavate&nbsp;Vasudevaya&#8221;<\/em>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><em>&#8220;Om Namo\u00a0Bhagavate\u00a0Vasudevaya&#8221;<\/em>\u00a0<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><em>nama\u00a0om\u00a0vishnu-padaya\u00a0krishna-preshthaya\u00a0bhu-tale<\/em>\u00a0<br><em>srimate\u00a0Bhaktivedanta-svamin\u00a0iti\u00a0namine<\/em>\u00a0<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><em>namas\u00a0te\u00a0sarasvate\u00a0deve\u00a0gaura-vani-pracharine<\/em> \u00a0<br><em>nirvishesha-shunyavadi-pashchatya-desha-tarine<\/em>\u00a0<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><em>\u015br\u012b-k\u1e5b\u1e63\u1e47a-caitanya\u00a0prabhu-nity\u0101nanda\u00a0<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><em>\u015br\u012b-advaita\u00a0gad\u0101dhara\u00a0\u015br\u012bv\u0101s\u0101di-gaura-bhakta-v\u1e5bnda<\/em>\u00a0<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><em>Hare Krishna Hare Krishna&nbsp;Krishna&nbsp;Krishna&nbsp;Hare&nbsp;Hare<\/em>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><em>Hare Rama Hare Rama&nbsp;Rama&nbsp;Rama&nbsp;Hare&nbsp;Hare<\/em>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><strong>SB 11.10.19<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">yadi\u00a0pr\u0101pti\u1e41\u00a0vigh\u0101ta\u1e41\u00a0ca\u00a0<br>j\u0101nanti\u00a0sukha-du\u1e25khayo\u1e25\u00a0<br>te\u202f\u2019py\u00a0addh\u0101\u00a0na\u00a0vidur\u00a0yoga\u1e41\u00a0<br>m\u1e5btyur\u00a0na\u00a0prabhaved\u00a0yath\u0101\u00a0\u00a0<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><strong>Translation:<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">Even if people know how to achieve happiness and avoid unhappiness, they still do not know the process by which death will not be able to exert its power over them.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><strong>Purport:<\/strong><em>&nbsp;<\/em>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">If the so-called intelligent materialists know the means of achieving&nbsp;happiness and destroying unhappiness, then they should deliver people from inevitable death.&nbsp;The scientists&nbsp;are busily working to solve this problem, but since they have completely failed, it is understood that they are not actually intelligent and that they do not know the means of achieving happiness and&nbsp;eliminating&nbsp;misery. It is most foolish to think that one can be happy with an axe&nbsp;hanging over one\u2019s neck. Lord&nbsp;K\u1e5bi\u1e63h\u1e47a&nbsp;says in&nbsp;Bhagavad-g\u012bt\u0101,&nbsp;m\u1e5btyu\u1e25&nbsp;sarva-hara\u015b&nbsp;c\u0101ham:&nbsp;\u201cI Myself come before you as death and take everything away.\u201d We should not blindly ignore the disaster of material life, but should instead accept the Lord\u2019s causeless mercy, which He so magnanimously offers in His incarnation as Chaitanya&nbsp;Mah\u0101prabhu. We should surrender to the lotus feet of Lord Chaitanya, who offers the real means for achieving unqualified happiness: the chanting of the holy names of the Lord. This is the Lord\u2019s desire, and it is in our own self-interest to take up this process.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\"><strong>HH Bhanu Swami Maharaj:<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">So&nbsp;the statement here is that,&nbsp;even if you know how to avoid the extreme happiness and distress, that is, avoid the unhappiness and get the happiness, still one cannot prevent death. Of course, death itself is a cause of suffering. So, technically, even if we are to avoid unhappiness and get happiness in life, we have death to confront or we cannot really be happy.&nbsp;&nbsp;This is an obvious fact.&nbsp;In spite of&nbsp;that, people&nbsp;ignore.&nbsp;So, this is a question which the Yaksha asked Yudhishthira.&nbsp;So, the Yaksha asked Yudhishthira,&nbsp;what&nbsp;is the most astonishing thing in this world?&nbsp;So, Yudhishthira replied, the most astonishing thing is that even though people see everybody else dying, they&nbsp;think,&nbsp;I will not die.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">So, this is related to the fact that we may see many things, unless we experience it&nbsp;ourself, we don&#8217;t really believe in them.&nbsp;So, a person sees other people go to prison for stealing or cheating or whatever, but he will go out and steal anyway.&nbsp;Then, when he goes to&nbsp;prison, then&nbsp;he realizes, oh, this was not so good,&nbsp;because now&nbsp;I&#8217;m&nbsp;really suffering. So, seeing is not enough.&nbsp;We often&nbsp;have to&nbsp;experience. The problem is that even after we&nbsp;experience,&nbsp;still we&nbsp;do not learn. A person goes to prison and suffers, then he comes out, then he thinks, oh, that was not so bad after all.&nbsp;Then he commits another crime, then he goes to prison again. This, of course, is foolish, but this is the nature of&nbsp;the human being. Sometimes, it takes us a long time to learn something, and only after many experiences then we will learn.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">So, of course, we see that people are in the material world without beginning. This means&nbsp;they&#8217;ve&nbsp;been trying to learn for a long, long time. And each time they experience happiness and distress, they also experience death, but then they live another life, and they experience the same things again, and another death, and another death, and they still&nbsp;don&#8217;t.&nbsp;So, when&nbsp;Yudhishtira&nbsp;says,&nbsp;it&#8217;s&nbsp;very astonishing,&nbsp;it&#8217;s&nbsp;not just astonishing that they&nbsp;don&#8217;t&nbsp;believe&nbsp;they&#8217;re&nbsp;going to die.&nbsp;Throughout life also, they&nbsp;don&#8217;t&nbsp;believe that&nbsp;they&#8217;re&nbsp;going to&nbsp;suffer, but they think&nbsp;somehow&nbsp;I can be happy. This&nbsp;happens&nbsp;life after life.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">So, it is a very slow process to learn.\u00a0And, of course, it also takes some intelligence.\u00a0The more\u00a0one is in ignorance,\u00a0the less likely it is to learn anything.\u00a0So, therefore, the lower species of life, they\u00a0don&#8217;t\u00a0learn anything, they just automatically progress. But the human being, because he has higher intelligence, can progress upwards and he can upgrade himself. And he should learn to progress. So, that first step is the\u00a0Varnashram\u00a0system and Karma Yoga, where one learns how to get a\u00a0higher\u00a0planets, a higher degree of happiness and less suffering. And one does that by avoiding sinful activities. So, just to come to that stage of learning takes a long time.\u00a0And as it goes to the\u00a0Varnashram\u00a0system, from\u00a0tamo\u00a0guna\u00a0to\u00a0rajo\u00a0guna\u00a0to\u00a0sattva\u00a0guna, which means from ignorance to knowledge, then gradually our intelligence becomes more. It becomes more possible to learn from our experiences as we progress through the\u00a0gunas. So, this is the process and it is\u00a0very, very long.\u00a0And that is because\u00a0the Jiva\u00a0is\u00a0very attached\u00a0to his enjoyment in this world. So, though we have this gradual system of elevation, because the\u00a0Jivas\u00a0are very slow learners, Krishna also makes a little exception. Of course, when the Lord comes and kills\u00a0demons, then\u00a0they get\u00a0real quick\u00a0advancement.\u00a0<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">But the other process is the process of\u00a0Bhakti. So, this allows\u00a0the\u00a0Jiva\u00a0to progress very, very rapidly. Of course, because we start with a lot of material influence, there will be some struggle in the beginning.\u00a0In other words, we still have\u00a0the\u00a0slow learning tendency\u00a0in the beginning. But as the devotee advances, then the process of learning becomes very quick. Therefore, Krishna in Bhagavad Gita says that, even if the devotee makes a mistake and falls, if he continues to do the\u00a0Bhakti, then the Lord\u00a0doesn&#8217;t\u00a0prescribe any purification.\u00a0So, Krishna expects that the devotee, through his experience, will learn something and not make the same mistake. So, this, we can say, is the mercy of the Supreme Lord and the process of\u00a0Bhakti.\u00a0Similarly, we have the\u00a0government\u00a0and they have laws and if you commit crimes, you go to jail.\u00a0But at the same time, we know that the judge, if he knows the person has a good character or whatever, then the punishment is much less.\u00a0So, the process of\u00a0Bhakti\u00a0is a manifestation of Krishna&#8217;s mercy.\u00a0<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">Unfortunately, some people are not qualified to accept that mercy.&nbsp;So&nbsp;in the story of&nbsp;Nalakuvera, they&nbsp;get&nbsp;cursed by&nbsp;Narada&nbsp;Muni&nbsp;and&nbsp;there&nbsp;he&nbsp;states&nbsp;that&nbsp;pride and&nbsp;wealth&nbsp;is&nbsp;the cause of&nbsp;so&nbsp;many&nbsp;other faults.&nbsp;Due to that intoxication&nbsp;with&nbsp;wealth&nbsp;we&nbsp;become&nbsp;blind&nbsp;and we have no interest at all in anything spiritual. And for that reason, the two sons of&nbsp;Kubera, they&nbsp;disrespected&nbsp;Narada&nbsp;Muni.&nbsp;So, if one is covered up so much by ignorance, then one cannot appreciate&nbsp;Bhakti&nbsp;or the devotee.&nbsp;Nevertheless, we also see that&nbsp;there is a remedy.&nbsp;So,&nbsp;Narada&nbsp;Muni says, well, if you take away the wealth, then they will lose their pride.&nbsp;When they&nbsp;have no wealth and they&nbsp;are suffering&nbsp;then they&nbsp;understand how&nbsp;everybody else&nbsp;is&nbsp;suffering&nbsp;and&nbsp;therefore&nbsp;they&nbsp;give-up&nbsp;violence to other living&nbsp;entity. Therefore,&nbsp;the solution for people who are proud of their wealth is to take all their wealth away.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">So,\u00a0Narada\u00a0Muni took all the wealth of the sons of\u00a0Kubera\u00a0away and they became trees. But he gave them a blessing.\u00a0One\u00a0is\u00a0they\u00a0retained\u00a0their memory. So, with that memory, they had a very great advantage.\u00a0So,\u00a0Narada\u00a0Muni arranged that after a hundred\u00a0devata years, they would meet Krishna.\u00a0And when they met Krishna,\u00a0then they offered\u00a0respects,\u00a0they\u00a0understood\u00a0the value of\u00a0Bhakti.\u00a0At\u00a0first\u00a0they were unqualified for any sort of mercy, but\u00a0later on, by the mercy of\u00a0Narada\u00a0Muni and their continued memory, they got some intelligence.\u00a0And then they were able to respect Krishna\u00a0and devotees.\u00a0So, for those who are unqualified for\u00a0Bhakti,\u00a0then\u00a0they will have to continue to stay in the material world and after that time hopefully by some continual mercy of devotees eventually they will develop faith.\u00a0Unfortunately,\u00a0the Lord does not\u00a0appear at all times\u00a0therefore the\u00a0Kuberas\u00a0had to wait for a hundred\u00a0devata\u00a0years. It\u00a0was\u00a0a long time.\u00a0So\u00a0Krishna appeared 5,000 years ago.\u00a0He\u00a0won&#8217;t\u00a0appear until another day of Brahma.\u00a0\u00a0<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">So\u00a0we cannot wait until that time to get saved.\u00a0So\u00a0Krishna\u00a0provides\u00a0another way,\u00a0besides taking away people&#8217;s wealth.\u00a0The other way\u00a0is\u00a0association with devotees. By that\u00a0association\u00a0those people who have\u00a0pride\u00a0can very quickly advance.\u00a0So\u00a0the Lord provides another advantage as well.\u00a0And that is, in Kali Yuga Caitanya\u00a0Mahaprabhu\u00a0manifests\u00a0Nama\u00a0Sankirtan.\u00a0So\u00a0this is another way in which Krishna manifests His presence.\u00a0The devotees\u00a0are considered to be\u00a0the best tirtha,\u00a0because within them the Lord is\u00a0residing.\u00a0If we\u00a0can&#8217;t\u00a0directly meet the\u00a0Lord,\u00a0at least\u00a0we meet devotees.\u00a0<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">The other way we meet Krishna is through chanting the name.\u00a0So\u00a0it is said that the Lord does not appear in Kali\u00a0Yuga,\u00a0but He appears in the form of\u00a0Nama.\u00a0So\u00a0by\u00a0chanting\u00a0the name of\u00a0Krishna\u00a0we can realize the form.\u00a0So\u00a0this is not only a method of contacting the Lord,\u00a0it is\u00a0also the easiest method of contacting the Lord. Of all different processes, chanting the name is the most powerful.\u00a0It is available for everybody. And it is even available for the lower\u00a0species\u00a0of life. So\u00a0Haridas\u00a0Thakur explained that loud chanting is\u00a0very good,\u00a0because all living entities get the advantage of hearing the name.\u00a0But\u00a0of course,\u00a0the effect on\u00a0the human being\u00a0is much greater. If it falls on the ears of an ignorant person,\u00a0even\u00a0then it has great power. If it falls on the ears of\u00a0a\u00a0person\u00a0who has\u00a0faith\u00a0then it has\u00a0more\u00a0power.\u00a0In any\u00a0case\u00a0it is available for all people. And this is unlike other processes. But for that\u00a0reason\u00a0it is also\u00a0the Yuga\u00a0Dharma.\u00a0\u00a0<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">So&nbsp;of course,&nbsp;in&nbsp;previous&nbsp;Yugas,&nbsp;they had a&nbsp;Varnashram&nbsp;system in effect.&nbsp;So&nbsp;the process of meditation and&nbsp;sacrifices&nbsp;and deity worship were all for people within the&nbsp;Varnashram.&nbsp;&nbsp;In Kali&nbsp;Yuga&nbsp;that system is destroyed. We see that in Bhagavatam in the 9th Canto and then after in the 12th Canto,&nbsp;there is the&nbsp;Yadu&nbsp;dynasty&nbsp;and&nbsp;how in Kali Yuga the family of&nbsp;Swayambhuva&nbsp;Manu dwindled away.&nbsp;So&nbsp;the Holy Name has influenced&nbsp;in spite of the&nbsp;disappearance of the&nbsp;Varnashram.&nbsp;Therefore&nbsp;it is&nbsp;recommended in&nbsp;Kali Yuga.&nbsp;Because it is available, everyone does not need a lesser form.&nbsp;Actually&nbsp;it is more powerful.&nbsp;And it not only is powerful,&nbsp;but it can elevate one to the highest position. That is&nbsp;the reason&nbsp;sometimes the Devatas pray to be born in Kali Yuga because they can get something that people&nbsp;don&#8217;t&nbsp;attain&nbsp;in other Yugas.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">Therefore,&nbsp;ultimately chanting&nbsp;the name is the way in which you can overcome the problem mentioned in this verse.&nbsp;What is described here is very typical of the people in Kali Yuga. They have less intelligence.&nbsp;Therefore,&nbsp;it is&nbsp;very difficult&nbsp;for them to escape from the suffering.&nbsp;So&nbsp;chanting the name of Krishna not only destroys the suffering,&nbsp;but it takes one to the highest levels of spiritual happiness.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">Hare&nbsp;Krishna&nbsp;!&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><strong>Q &amp; A:<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\"><strong>1.)&nbsp;Thank&nbsp;you&nbsp;Maharaj. Maharaj, you said in the case of&nbsp;Nalakuvera&nbsp;and&nbsp;Manigriva, the memory of their past sins helped them to overcome and of course it took a longer&nbsp;time. But we see Krishna also gives all the living entities forgetfulness by which they&nbsp;don&#8217;t&nbsp;remember their past.&nbsp;So&nbsp;in one&nbsp;sense,&nbsp;one perspective is&nbsp;it&#8217;s&nbsp;better to have the memory of the past sins so that one can correct themselves which has been going on for millions of lifetimes Maharaj.&nbsp;How&nbsp;to&nbsp;appreciate that?&nbsp;<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">People know their whole&nbsp;life&nbsp;and they go to prison once and they come out of prison.&nbsp;In spite of&nbsp;the&nbsp;memory,&nbsp;they&nbsp;don&#8217;t&nbsp;learn anything.&nbsp;Some people can take advantage of their&nbsp;memory. Others&nbsp;don&#8217;t.&nbsp;So&nbsp;the arrangement according to body to body is in&nbsp;general,&nbsp;the&nbsp;previous&nbsp;memories are not there.&nbsp;The influence is still there.&nbsp;One&nbsp;may not remember&nbsp;particular incidents&nbsp;from&nbsp;previous&nbsp;lifetimes,&nbsp;but nevertheless certain impressions are there which stay with you and influence your life.&nbsp;Some&nbsp;of those influences are kept with you so that in this lifetime you can make some improvements.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">If all of the memories and everything were all&nbsp;available,&nbsp;then it would be useless.&nbsp;We would not be able to concentrate on this lifetime. We would be constantly afflicted by all the many thousands and thousands of lifetimes and experiences.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\"><strong>2.)&nbsp;Maharaj, you mentioned that chanting the holy name is the most powerful.&nbsp;On the other hand, we know that the association of the devotee is&nbsp;also very&nbsp;very&nbsp;powerful, so, how is it in&nbsp;comparison&nbsp;or in relation to each&nbsp;other ?&nbsp;<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">Association&nbsp;of the devotees means,&nbsp;ultimately&nbsp;the&nbsp;teaching. Ultimate teaching&nbsp;should be to chant the holy name.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\"><strong>3.)&nbsp;Maharaj, in relation to the holy name, I was just reading a verse from Chaitanya&nbsp;Bhagavata. Lord Caitanya says this verse,&nbsp;\u201c<\/strong><strong><em>sarva-ksana&nbsp;bala\u2019&nbsp;ithe&nbsp;vidhi&nbsp;nahi&nbsp;ara\u201d(CB &#8211;&nbsp;2.23.78)<\/em><\/strong><em>.&nbsp;<\/em><strong><em>T<\/em><\/strong><strong>here&nbsp;is&nbsp;no other rules but to chant the holy name at all times.&nbsp;Which means, is that a rule Maharaj, at all times one should chant the holy name?&nbsp;<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">Of course, we have other processes as well.&nbsp;But we give&nbsp;a prominence&nbsp;to the chanting of the name.&nbsp;For instance, though chanting is the main process, we have hearing and we have deity worship.&nbsp;But&nbsp;these act&nbsp;as&nbsp;a&nbsp;assistant&nbsp;to&nbsp;chanting.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\"><strong>Devotee:&nbsp;<\/strong>Thank&nbsp;you Maharaj.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\"><strong>HH Bhanu Swami&nbsp;Maharaj:<\/strong>&nbsp;Hare&nbsp;Krishna&nbsp;!&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\"><strong>Devotees :<\/strong>&nbsp;Granthraj&nbsp;Sri&nbsp;Srimad&nbsp;Bhagavatham&nbsp;ki&nbsp;Jai&nbsp;!!&nbsp;HH Banu Swami Maharaj ki&nbsp;Jai&nbsp;!!&nbsp;His Divine Grace A.C.&nbsp;Bhaktivedanta&nbsp;Swami&nbsp;Srila&nbsp;Prabhupad&nbsp;ki&nbsp;Jai&nbsp;!!&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Srimad&nbsp;Bhagavatam \u2013 11.10.19 | HH Bhanu Swami Maharaj | ISKCON Chennai | April 7, 2021&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &#8220;Om Namo&nbsp;Bhagavate&nbsp;Vasudevaya&#8221;&nbsp; &#8220;Om Namo&nbsp;Bhagavate&nbsp;Vasudevaya&#8221;&nbsp; &#8220;Om Namo\u00a0Bhagavate\u00a0Vasudevaya&#8221;\u00a0 nama\u00a0om\u00a0vishnu-padaya\u00a0krishna-preshthaya\u00a0bhu-tale\u00a0srimate\u00a0Bhaktivedanta-svamin\u00a0iti\u00a0namine\u00a0 namas\u00a0te\u00a0sarasvate\u00a0deve\u00a0gaura-vani-pracharine \u00a0nirvishesha-shunyavadi-pashchatya-desha-tarine\u00a0 \u015br\u012b-k\u1e5b\u1e63\u1e47a-caitanya\u00a0prabhu-nity\u0101nanda\u00a0 \u015br\u012b-advaita\u00a0gad\u0101dhara\u00a0\u015br\u012bv\u0101s\u0101di-gaura-bhakta-v\u1e5bnda\u00a0 Hare Krishna Hare Krishna&nbsp;Krishna&nbsp;Krishna&nbsp;Hare&nbsp;Hare&nbsp; Hare Rama Hare Rama&nbsp;Rama&nbsp;Rama&nbsp;Hare&nbsp;Hare&nbsp; SB 11.10.19&nbsp; yadi\u00a0pr\u0101pti\u1e41\u00a0vigh\u0101ta\u1e41\u00a0ca\u00a0j\u0101nanti\u00a0sukha-du\u1e25khayo\u1e25\u00a0te\u202f\u2019py\u00a0addh\u0101\u00a0na\u00a0vid